{{Sangam literature}}
'''Keerandhaiyar''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: கீரந்தையார்) was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom a sole verse of the Sangam literature has been attributed, in addition to verse 19 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages = 31–32 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Keerandhaiyar is believed to have belonged to the Brahmin caste of the Keerar tribe, who changed their occupation from yagna to [[performing arts]]. These people primarily spoke [[Sanskrit]] but have adapted themselves to the [[Tamil culture]] and language. He belonged to the [[Aryan race]] who had come down south and settled down in the Tamil land since antiquity. There were about 24 poets of the Sangam era who belonged to this tribe, including Nakkirar I and Kanakkaayanar.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = குறுந்தொகை, பரிபாடல், கலித்தொகை [Kurunthogai, Paripadal, Kalitthogai] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 2 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 240–242 (Book II) | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Keerandhaiyar has written a sole Sangam verse, namely, verse 2 of [[Paripaadal]] praising [[Lord Vishnu]], besides verse 19 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]] in praise of [[Valluvar]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/>
